GWFL RRD-Graph README
--------------------

1. Purpose

RRD-Graph is basically just a Perl CGI script used to represent the
data stored by FIFO-RRD as graphs via the Nagios interface.

2. Requirements

* Perl 5
* CGI enabled web server (ie. Apache)
* The following Perl modules: POSIX, RRDs
* Access to FIFO-RRD's template_config.pm & Validate.pm

3. Compiling and Installation

a) mv rrd-graph.cgi /path/to/nagios/cgi
b) mv *.pm /path/to/fifo-rrd/installation
c) Configure graph_templates.pm and rrd-graph.pl
d) Make sure rrd-graph.cgi can write to the FIFO-RRD storage directory
   and the graph image directory (under the webroot).

Refer to http://gwfl.daimonic.org/?p=doc for an implementation example.

4. Author

Gary Wall <gary@daimonic.org>


